      "text": "A 78-year-old man is brought to the Emergency Department with two days of melena, dizziness, and weakness. He has chronic kidney disease and a history of aortic stenosis. Examination reveals pallor. Esophagogastroduodenoscopy shows no significant lesions, but colonoscopy reveals multiple small vascular ectasias in the cecum consistent with angiodysplasia. He continues to pass dark, tarry stools despite fluid resuscitation and two units of packed red blood cells (see lab result).\n\n\nHeart rate\n115/min\n\n\nBlood pressure\n90/60 mm Hg\n\n\n\n\nTest\nResult\nNormal Values\n\n\nHemoglobin\n80 g/L\n130 - 170 g/L\n\n\nAfter discussion with gastroenterology, what is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Selective mesenteric angiography with embolization"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Repeat colonoscopic evaluation for thermal coagulation"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Surgical resection of the cecum"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "High-dose intravenous proton pump inhibitor infusion"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g80FN3&anker=Zde24e8c01b800ecade89c0624562763d\" data-learningcard-id=\"g80FN3\" data-anker=\"Zde24e8c01b800ecade89c0624562763d\" data-sememe-id=\"j9Y_Mr\">Angiodysplasia</a>, a vascular <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vo0AdS&anker=Za2917144496685a377f046c65f8f8102\" data-learningcard-id=\"vo0AdS\" data-anker=\"Za2917144496685a377f046c65f8f8102\" data-section-id=\"f6ck4W0\" data-sememe-id=\"cHXa6z\">malformation</a> often found in the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=R60lkS&anker=Z0b8de50768bf52d47269e521fc53df52\" data-learningcard-id=\"R60lkS\" data-anker=\"Z0b8de50768bf52d47269e521fc53df52\" data-section-id=\"K8cUnV0\" data-sememe-id=\"DPc1Sc0\">cecum</a> and right <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=R60lkS&anker=Ze19293358dc6c65dc95f936bb8fca493\" data-learningcard-id=\"R60lkS\" data-anker=\"Ze19293358dc6c65dc95f936bb8fca493\" data-section-id=\"K8cUnV0\" data-sememe-id=\"wPchSc0\">colon</a>, is associated with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lg0vv2&anker=Zeb975888cde4515672ab89a7a3068ab2\" data-learningcard-id=\"lg0vv2\" data-anker=\"Zeb975888cde4515672ab89a7a3068ab2\" data-sememe-id=\"W40PRT\">chronic kidney disease</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Zh0Zcf&anker=Zfb3b3131a3e792dfe1bf5db3f18030e0\" data-learningcard-id=\"Zh0Zcf\" data-anker=\"Zfb3b3131a3e792dfe1bf5db3f18030e0\" data-sememe-id=\"rwYf4r\">aortic stenosis</a>. This patient presents with significant <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZS0Zy2&anker=Z5b38a059d860d4f7f79d2947306c643e\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZS0Zy2\" data-anker=\"Z5b38a059d860d4f7f79d2947306c643e\" data-sememe-id=\"M40MPT\">gastrointestinal bleeding</a>, evidenced by <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZS0Zy2&anker=Z39f22768286d3e3202467c988d3be66a\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZS0Zy2\" data-anker=\"Z39f22768286d3e3202467c988d3be66a\" data-section-id=\"9E0NB3\" data-sememe-id=\"jF0_33\">melena</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rM0fJg&anker=Zb5022b8fa3fa419ab039a0f8d70866a2\" data-learningcard-id=\"rM0fJg\" data-anker=\"Zb5022b8fa3fa419ab039a0f8d70866a2\" data-section-id=\"oVc0vY0\" data-sememe-id=\"nGb7-E\">hypotension</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rM0fJg&anker=Z3ae4e1e5581c7405590e65b57fa82021\" data-learningcard-id=\"rM0fJg\" data-anker=\"Z3ae4e1e5581c7405590e65b57fa82021\" data-section-id=\"KVcUvY0\" data-sememe-id=\"lNbvY8\">tachycardia</a>. Selective <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=LJ0wuS&anker=Z2e7145689ecdf9560060a209d9ae676a\" data-learningcard-id=\"LJ0wuS\" data-anker=\"Z2e7145689ecdf9560060a209d9ae676a\" data-section-id=\"Ja1sl20\" data-sememe-id=\"xjXEcy\">mesenteric</a> <span data-sememe-id=\"dWbo4s\">angiography</span> offers both diagnostic and therapeutic benefits by localizing bleeding vessels and enabling direct embolization to arrest hemorrhage. This approach is particularly effective when bleeding persists despite initial stabilization and when endoscopic therapy is less effective due to the intermittent and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Za466a64a9ff741e0365c57cc1db2aa1b\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Za466a64a9ff741e0365c57cc1db2aa1b\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">superficial</a> nature of angiodysplastic lesions.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point: </b></span>In cases of significant <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZS0Zy2&anker=Z5b38a059d860d4f7f79d2947306c643e\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZS0Zy2\" data-anker=\"Z5b38a059d860d4f7f79d2947306c643e\" data-sememe-id=\"M40MPT\">gastrointestinal bleeding</a> due to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g80FN3&anker=Zde24e8c01b800ecade89c0624562763d\" data-learningcard-id=\"g80FN3\" data-anker=\"Zde24e8c01b800ecade89c0624562763d\" data-sememe-id=\"j9Y_Mr\">angiodysplasia</a>, especially in <span data-sememe-id=\"3LdSxq0\">hemodynamically unstable</span> patients, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=LJ0wuS&anker=Z2e7145689ecdf9560060a209d9ae676a\" data-learningcard-id=\"LJ0wuS\" data-anker=\"Z2e7145689ecdf9560060a209d9ae676a\" data-section-id=\"Ja1sl20\" data-sememe-id=\"xjXEcy\">mesenteric</a> <span data-sememe-id=\"i5WJPN0\">angioembolization</span> is an effective and minimally invasive treatment option to control bleeding.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Endoscopic thermal coagulation is used for focal bleeding lesions, but this patient has multiple small vascular ectasias. The diffuse nature of the lesions reduces the <span data-sememe-id=\"NfW-mk0\">efficacy</span> of repeat localized thermal therapy, especially given the patient's ongoing <span data-sememe-id=\"3LdSxq0\">hemodynamic instability</span> and blood loss.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Surgical resection is considered for localized lesions but is not ideal for diffuse <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g80FN3&anker=Zde24e8c01b800ecade89c0624562763d\" data-learningcard-id=\"g80FN3\" data-anker=\"Zde24e8c01b800ecade89c0624562763d\" data-sememe-id=\"j9Y_Mr\">angiodysplasia</a>. The patient has multiple small vascular lesions, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgery</a> poses significant perioperative risks, especially given the patient's age and comorbidities. Less invasive interventions should be exhausted first.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rm0fSg&anker=Z2753e50142e2f5b7089b165accdcc900\" data-learningcard-id=\"rm0fSg\" data-anker=\"Z2753e50142e2f5b7089b165accdcc900\" data-sememe-id=\"ML0Myg\">Proton pump inhibitors</a> are effective for acid-mediated lesions, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zg0rB2&anker=Zff8a777f774160654aae94375bc8ccab\" data-learningcard-id=\"zg0rB2\" data-anker=\"Zff8a777f774160654aae94375bc8ccab\" data-sememe-id=\"m40VPT\">peptic ulcers</a>, by reducing <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=M60MlS&anker=Z2b222329949064378f320c11017a71ee\" data-learningcard-id=\"M60MlS\" data-anker=\"Z2b222329949064378f320c11017a71ee\" data-section-id=\"O8cI5V0\" data-sememe-id=\"pmXLgA\">gastric acid</a> secretion. However, the bleeding source here is <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=R60lkS&anker=Ze19293358dc6c65dc95f936bb8fca493\" data-learningcard-id=\"R60lkS\" data-anker=\"Ze19293358dc6c65dc95f936bb8fca493\" data-section-id=\"K8cUnV0\" data-sememe-id=\"wPchSc0\">colonic</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g80FN3&anker=Zde24e8c01b800ecade89c0624562763d\" data-learningcard-id=\"g80FN3\" data-anker=\"Zde24e8c01b800ecade89c0624562763d\" data-sememe-id=\"j9Y_Mr\">angiodysplasia</a>, a vascular abnormality, not an acid-related lesion. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rm0fSg&anker=Z2753e50142e2f5b7089b165accdcc900\" data-learningcard-id=\"rm0fSg\" data-anker=\"Z2753e50142e2f5b7089b165accdcc900\" data-sememe-id=\"ML0Myg\">PPIs</a> do not address the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vo0AdS&anker=Z4617e4b27255a30946edb12a68ce139d\" data-learningcard-id=\"vo0AdS\" data-anker=\"Z4617e4b27255a30946edb12a68ce139d\" data-section-id=\"f6ck4W0\" data-sememe-id=\"CUbq2G\">arteriovenous malformations</a> seen in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=g80FN3&anker=Zde24e8c01b800ecade89c0624562763d\" data-learningcard-id=\"g80FN3\" data-anker=\"Zde24e8c01b800ecade89c0624562763d\" data-sememe-id=\"j9Y_Mr\">angiodysplasia</a>.</div>",
